# Large artifacts are distributed via Google Cloud Storage (GCS) buckets
# See docs/MODEL_HOSTING.md for details on downloading models

# Shell scripts MUST use LF line endings even on Windows checkouts.
# Without this rule, Windows users with `core.autocrlf=true` get CRLF
# converted into .sh files on checkout. When those files get COPYed
# into a Linux container image, the shebang line becomes `#!/bin/bash\r`,
# which Linux exec interprets as a request for the (nonexistent)
# interpreter `bash\r`. The container then dies at startup with the
# notoriously misleading error:
#
#   exec /app/docker_entrypoint.sh: no such file or directory
#
# Forcing eol=lf on .sh files (and their Dockerfile sibling) avoids the
# cross-platform footgun entirely.
*.sh           text eol=lf
Dockerfile     text eol=lf

